                            <comment id="18015" author="jtinpc" created="Wed, 14 Jun 2006 05:12:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve learned more about this now.  The type is not being seen as Boolean because there is a custom property editor registered which converts the values to text (and back).  So that makes sense.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, specifying the value=&quot;true&quot; worked in M4 and now doesn&apos;t.  That seems like a problem - the form backing object value is being converted to the text string &quot;false&quot;, but the checkbox shows &quot;checked&quot; status anyway.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
